The returned array `answer` is not null.
The length of the returned array `answer` is equal to the length of the input array `queries`.
Each element in the returned array `answer` is either true or false.
The value of `answer[i]` is true if it is possible to make `s` a palindrome by performing operations specified by the `i-th` query.
The value of `answer[i]` is false if it is not possible to make `s` a palindrome by performing operations specified by the `i-th` query.
